# Credentials for RECORDING protocol-conversion cassettes (local only).
#
# These are never needed to RUN the tests — `make go-conversion-tests` replays
# committed cassettes offline with no keys. They are only used by
# `make go-conversion-update`, which hits real providers to (re)record cassettes
# and regenerate golden files.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env        # then fill in real values below
#   set -a && source .env && set +a
#   make go-conversion-update RUN=anthropic__openai   # record one provider
#
# NEVER commit .env (it is gitignored). Cassettes store only response bodies and
# non-sensitive request metadata — no API keys — so they are safe to commit.

# --- Generic defaults (record one provider at a time) ---
NYRO_TEST_API_KEY=
NYRO_TEST_BASE_URL=
NYRO_TEST_MODEL=

# --- Optional per-provider overrides (record multiple providers in one run) ---
# Provider name is the upstream provider id, uppercased. Falls back to the
# generic vars above when unset.
#
# NYRO_TEST_OPENAI_API_KEY=
# NYRO_TEST_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com
# NYRO_TEST_OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o
#
# NYRO_TEST_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# NYRO_TEST_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com
# NYRO_TEST_ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022
